@Node Kurz "SoftRAM: 1. Short description"

SoftRAM is able to increase your RAM space by simply  compressing  all
currently   unused   memory   spaces.  A  brand  new  state-of-the-art
compressing algorithm provides high compression rates, though it is as
fast as lightning!

Since a very special memory mapping algorithm is  used,  SoftRAM  also
works on Amiga's without MMU!

A RAM doubler came first out on  Macintosh,  quickly  followed  by  PC
implementations. Now, even Amiga users have the privilege to use a RAM
doubler!

