@Node Install "SoftRAM: 3. Installation and Program Start"

AmigaOS 2.04 is required to use this  program.  There  is  no  special
processor required, but you should have some RAM in your machine!

Simply copy the "SoftRAM" file into your C: drawer.  If  you  want  to
double your RAM space, open a new Shell and type "SoftRAM".

SoftRAM requires some seconds to check the system and compress the RAM
blocks  that  are already allocated. After that, SoftRAM tells you the
current compression rate.

You can stop SoftRAM by pressing <CTRL>-<C>. It  tries  to  decompress
all compressed RAM blocks.

